Cape Town - A gruesome discovery was made when a newborn baby was found inside a rubbish bag in Bloemfontein on Thursday afternoon. It is believed that the baby was discovered by a man who had opened the refuse bag to search its contents. "Upon further assessment, paramedics found a newborn baby wrapped in a plastic bag inside the rubbish bag. Unfortunately, nothing more could be done by paramedics and the baby was declared dead at the scene," said ER24 in a statement. Also read: Newborn baby found in plastic bag in Centurion Paramedics were called to the scene just after 17:00. The details surrounding the incident are not yet known and the police were on the scene for further investigations. IOL 